; A general N-gon procedure. Demonstrates:
;   - parameters (:N and :SIDE flow through to FORWARD and RIGHT)
;   - REPEAT closure detection — the inlay hint at the closing ']' should
;     read 'home' for any concrete N, because N · (360/N) = 360°.
;   - go-to-declaration: ⌘-click on POLYGON below jumps up to its TO line.

TO POLYGON :N :SIDE
  REPEAT :N [
    FORWARD :SIDE
    RIGHT 360 / :N
  ]
END

; Drive — try changing 6 to 5, 8, 12 and watch the hints update.
POLYGON 6 40
HOME
